#### Jenkins Installation
> Login to EC2 terminal 
> Update the OS
$ sudo apt update
> Install Java 
$ sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk -y
> Verify
$ jave -version
> Install jenkins > go to official jenkins website https://www.jenkins.io/doc/book/installing/
> select Linux > Debian/ubuntu
> First copy & paste below command in terminal to add jenkins keyrings
$ sudo wget -O /etc/apt/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc \
  https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/jenkins.io-2026.key
> Then copy below command to add binary of jenkins
$ echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc]" \
  https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/ | sudo tee \
  /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list > /dev/null
> Now update the OS & install Jenkins Using below command
$ sudo apt update
$ sudo apt install jenkins -y
> check the status of jenkins
$ sudo systemctl status jenkins
> Pess 'q' to exit screen
> If it is not active then activate jenkins using below command
$ sudo systemctl start jenkins
$ sudo systemctl enable jenkins
> go to browser type http://<ec2-pulic-ip>:8080 & hit the enter
> go back to terminal & type below command
$ sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
> copy the code and & enter to the jenkins UI password
> click on Install suggested Plugins
> Create First Admin User or Skip the step [If you want to use this Jenkins instance for future use-cases as well, better to create admin user]
> Jenkins is ready now 
########## Jenkins Installation is Succesfull

######## Docker installation steps
> Go to terminal & type below command 
$ sudo apt install docker.io -y
> check the docker status 
$ systemctl status docker
> It should show active, if not then type below command to activate
$ systemctl start docker
$ systemctl enable docker
> verify the docker 
$ docker --version
> test the docker 
$ sudo docker run hello-word
> If it prints Success message then docker works


########## Allow Jenkins to use Docker
> Add jenkins user to docker group
$ sudo usermod -aG docker jenkins

> Now restart both services (jenkins & docker)
$ sudo systemctl restart docker
$ sudo systemctl restart jenkins 

######### Verify Jenkins user can access Docker
> Switch jenkins user & type any docker command
$ sudo su - jenkins
$ sudo docker ps

>If it shows no permission error â†’ perfect.
> If permission denied appears:
> Run this and reboot:
$ sudo reboot

######### Successfully Configured Jenkins & Docker
